div1.p:
Q. Did you see him put his name to this? - A. I did;
John Staples
first proposed to me to make this purchase; he went with me to Morgan's house, near Walham Green, where I saw the horse; the prisoner not being at home, I left word with his wife, if he brought the horse to London, I might purchase it of him; in consequence of which the prisoner came the same afternoon, or on the next day, I am not positive which.
